config BR2_PACKAGE_PANICOS_INPUT_SENSE
	bool "panicos-input-sense"
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_BASH
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_EVTEST
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_PIPEWIRE && BR2_PACKAGE_WIREPLUMBER
	select BR2_PACKAGE_BASH
	select BR2_PACKAGE_EVTEST
	help
	  ROCKNIX's input_sense daemon, vendored verbatim. Listens to evdev
	  events from every input device on the system and routes special
	  keys: volume up/down (wpctl), volume mute, power button (fake
	  suspend), lid open/close, controller function-key combos
	  (brightness, screenshot, mangohud toggle, etc.).

	  We need this because handheld inputs (gpio-keys-volume,
	  axp20x-pek power button) don't route through sway by default —
	  sway-level bindsym only fires for keys that hit sway's libinput
	  pipeline. ROCKNIX's daemon reads evdev directly and side-steps
	  the WM entirely.

	  Source: third_party/rocknix/projects/ROCKNIX/packages/sysutils/
	  system-utils/sources/scripts/input_sense (and 001-functions
	  + sources/scripts/volume from packages/rocknix). Vendored with
	  two minimal adaptations: input_sense + volume source the
	  functions library from a private path
	  (/usr/lib/panicos-input-sense/) instead of /etc/profile to avoid
	  polluting global env, and `volume` calls `wpctl set-volume`
	  instead of `pactl --set-sink-volume` since we ship pipewire's
	  wpctl rather than pulseaudio-utils.

	  Many of the function-key actions invoke helpers that don't exist
	  on PanicOS yet (rocknix-fake-suspend, brightness, mango-notify,
	  screen_switch, ledcontrol, wifictl). Those handlers fail with
	  "command not found" — relevant key combos just no-op until the
	  helpers are stubbed in. Volume + mute work today; others come
	  online as we port the rest.
